  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Seminal works by Acemoglu and Restrepo (2018, 2022) and Autor (2019) provide insights into how automation reshapes labor markets, focusing on technology as a substitute for individual worker tasks or how workers and tasks can complement or substitute for technology.",
    "Eloundou et al. (2023) and Felten et al. (2023) provide excellent empirical analyses of which tasks are amenable to automation by the current wave of foundation models.",
    "These studies oer a useful lens for understanding the economic implications of AI before AGI is reached.",
    "Our contribution to these strands of literature is to look at the limit case of what happens if either all work tasks are automated or we asymptote towards a world in which all tasks are automated.",
    "Our paper is also related to a broader literature on AGI and superintelligence literature."
  ],
